  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Install 20 water cisterns in rural Puerto Rico</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water is life! Access to clean water in rural Puerto Rico is unstable due to constant power outages, exacerbated since Hurricane Maria in 2017. In this new context of COVID-19, combined with non-stop earthquakes and a hyperactive hurricane season, water becomes essential to the very survival of those that are at a higher risk when low hygiene conditions are present. We look to provide the means for some of the most vulnerable families to have access to water during service shutdowns.</narrative>
  </description>
